    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="53"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/158</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Perú</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poindexter</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1924</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received November 18.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 300</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the Department’s
                    cablegram No. 41 of September 11, 10 p.m., and to transmit herewith in Spanish
                    and translation copy of a note just received from the Foreign Office,<note
                        n="88" xml:id="d53fn88">Note not printed.</note> in response to
                    representations made by the Embassy as directed in the cabled instruction under
                    acknowledgment.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office note states that Don Glicerio Camino, Peruvian Chargé
                    d’Affaires at Prague, will represent Perú at the forthcoming conference in
                    Geneva for the further restriction in the traffic of narcotic drugs; and that
                    that part of the Embassy’s note relating <pb facs="0216" n="102" xml:id="pg_102"
                    /> to restriction in the cultivation of the coca leaf plant has been
                    communicated to the Ministry of Hacienda with a request for appropriate
                    action.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miles Poindexter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
